data.chText: 体面的；得体的；值得尊敬的
data.enText: considered by society to be acceptable, good or correct

data.chText: 去把自己弄得体面点儿。
data.enText: Go and make yourself look respectable.
fairly good; that there is not reason to be ashamed of

simple_means.memory_skill: re 一再 + spect 看 + able 可…的，respect的形容词 → 可敬的

ex.chText: 在学生眼里，他是一位勤勉可敬的老师。
ex.enText: According to his students, he is a hard-working and respectable teacher.

synonyms.bx: 指因品质、行为等高尚而应该得到他人尊敬的。

ex.chText: 他是过去10年中最受尊敬的篮球运动员之一。
ex.enText: He's one of the most respected basketball players in the last decade.

ex.chText: 她是一位广受尊敬的评论员。
ex.enText: She was a widely respected commentator.

synonyms.bx: 指因取得的成就而受人敬重的。

ex.chText: 他们安静地站着，以示尊敬。
他一向尊重女儿的独立。
ex.enText: He was always respectful of his daughter's independence.

synonyms.bx: 指对某人或某事物表示尊敬或敬意的。

tr: large in amount or extent or degree
characterized by socially or conventionally acceptable morals

value.def: Someone or something that is respectable is approved of by society and considered to be morally correct.

example.ex: He came from a perfectly respectable middle-class family...
example.tran: 他出身于一个非常正派的中产阶级家庭。

example.ex: It was a highly respectable and what was called an 'old-fashioned' hotel situated not far from Piccadilly.
example.tran: 这是一家非常体面的“老式”旅馆，坐落在离皮卡迪利广场不远的地方。

example.ex: She's respectably dressed in jeans and sweatshirt.
example.tran: 她穿着牛仔裤和运动衫，非常得体。

example.ex: If she divorced Tony, she would lose the respectability she had as Mrs Tony Tatterton.
example.tran: 如果她和托尼离婚，将失去她作为托尼·塔特滕夫人的名望。

value.def: You can say that something is respectable when you mean that it is good enough or acceptable.

example.ex: ...investments that offer respectable rates of return...
At last I have something respectable to wear!
example.tran: 我终于可以穿上体面的衣服了！

value.tran: 好的;可观的;令人满意的
